name: ethyl 4-cyanophenylacetate
Reason: 4-Cyanophenyl can increase the melting point due to the additional pi-system and rigidity, estimated at around +20 °C. The cyano group introduces a strong withdrawing group, increasing intermolecular forces and melting point by approximately +50 °C. The carbonyl group introduces polar carbonyl interactions, contributing approximately +40 °C. The methyl group reduces the melting point by approximately -10 °C due to the reduced molecular weight and the absence of a hydroxyl group.
